de.fuberlin.panda.metadata.result.fusion.temporal

Class TemporalClusterDetector

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.fuberlin.panda.metadata.result.fusion.clustering.ClusterDetector
      • de.fuberlin.panda.metadata.result.fusion.temporal.TemporalClusterDetector

  • public class TemporalClusterDetector
extends ClusterDetector
    This class is a subclass of ClusterDetector. It extends the ClusterDetector#detectClusters(Set) method for eliminating all temporal outliers without a timestamp. It also overrides the #calculateNeighborhood(ClusteringObject, Set) method.
    Since:
    28.01.2014
    Author:
    Sebastian Schulz
    See Also:
    TemporalClusterDetector(double, int), #detectClusters(Set), #eliminateOutliersWithoutTimestamp(Set), #calculateNeighborhood(ClusteringObject, Set)

      • eliminateOutliersWithoutTimestamp

        protected void eliminateOutliersWithoutTimestamp(java.util.TreeSet<? extends ClusteringObject> clusteringObjects)
        This method removes all TemporalClusteringObjects which doesn't have an expiration date timestamp (marked by timestamp = -1) from the Set of ClusteringObjects for further processing. It also marks the object as an outlier by setting its clusterId to NO_METADATA (-1) and adds it to the augmentedClusteringObjectList.
        Parameters:
        clusteringObjects - - a Set of ClusteringObjects which should be analyzed.

      • calculateNeighborhood

        protected void calculateNeighborhood(ClusteringObject clusteringObject,
                         java.util.TreeSet<? extends ClusteringObject> clusteringObjects)
        This method builds SortedSet of ClusteringObjects which represent the neighbors of a given ClusteringObject. It checks for each neighbor if its distance to the given object is less or equal the neighborhoodRadius and adds it to the set. The set is sorted by the helpEpsilonDistance which represents the distance from the given object to the neighbor. Because of that reason it is easier to calculate the core distance of a TemporaltClusteringObject.

        This method heavily influences the runtime of the OPTICS algorithm!
        Specified by:
        calculateNeighborhood in class ClusterDetector
        Parameters:
        clusteringObject - - the current ClusteringObject, which is in the center of the neighborhoodRadius.
        clusteringObjects - - a Set of ClusteringObjects which should be analyzed.
